<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-06-13T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-06-13T10:00:00-05:00" n="52" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d52">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">795A.5/6–1350: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Embassy in Korea</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#left">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        </seg>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-06-13T11:00:00-04:00">June 13,
                                1950—11 a. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>576. Pls. clarify urdesp. 456, May 4, 1950<note n="1" xml:id="d52fn1">Not
                            printed.</note> stating that “South Korean Army is superior today” to
                        North Korean Army and is better equipped. Intelligence available here as
                        well as most recent <gloss target="#t_KMAG1">KMAG</gloss> semi-annual
                            report<note n="2" xml:id="d52fn2">Reference is to the report for the
                            period ending December 31, 1949, which was transmitted to the Department
                            with despatch no. 99, January 26, from Seoul, not printed
                            (795.58/1–2650).</note> indicate that North Korean airpower and heavier
                        artillery make North Korean armed forces superior and capable of successful
                        operations against South.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>